WEBVTT

00:00.083 --> 00:02.166
<i>Previously on </i>Desperate Housewives.

00:02.250 --> 00:04.041
<i>Mike's therapy hit a snag.</i>

00:04.125 --> 00:05.709
I keep telling you, I don't remember.

00:05.792 --> 00:08.041
Something happened at that movie.
Who did you see it with?

00:08.125 --> 00:10.125
- Probably Susan.
- Why not ask her about it?

00:10.208 --> 00:12.875
- Mike, it wasn't a movie. That was us.
- What?

00:12.959 --> 00:14.834
That was the first night
that we spent together.

00:14.917 --> 00:18.291
I saw you watching us.
We were just talking.

00:18.375 --> 00:20.583
<i>Gabby saw another side of Victor.</i>

00:20.667 --> 00:22.667
I didn't marry an angry woman.
I just divorced one.

00:22.750 --> 00:24.917
And I set her up in a nice house,
I gave her an allowance.

00:25.000 --> 00:26.458
And then I came and went as I pleased.

00:26.542 --> 00:27.959
I've known you for two weeks,

00:28.041 --> 00:30.750
and this is the first glimpse of a guy
I could actually like.

00:30.834 --> 00:33.291
<i>Tom's back put him out of commission.</i>

00:33.375 --> 00:35.125
It'll be a while
before he's back on his feet.

00:35.208 --> 00:36.792
- How much of a while?
- Three months.

00:36.875 --> 00:40.083
<i>And Edie bared more than her soul</i>
<i>for Carlos.</i>

00:40.166 --> 00:42.875
I'm here and I'm asking for a chance.

00:48.291 --> 00:52.917
<i>Edie Britt had always thought</i>
<i>of herself as passionate.</i>

00:53.000 --> 00:55.041
<i>Aggressively,</i>

00:55.125 --> 00:57.166
<i>relentlessly,</i>

00:57.250 --> 00:59.375
<i>violently passionate.</i>

01:01.208 --> 01:05.542
<i>Carlos Solis had always thought</i>
<i>of himself as passionate.</i>

01:05.625 --> 01:07.709
<i>Romantically,</i>

01:07.792 --> 01:10.333
<i>spontaneously,</i>

01:10.417 --> 01:13.542
<i>constantly passionate.</i>

01:13.625 --> 01:19.125
<i>So it was natural for Edie and Carlos</i>
<i>to assume that if they ever had sex,</i>

01:19.208 --> 01:21.041
<i>it would be amazing.</i>

01:21.125 --> 01:24.750
<i>And in fact, it was.</i>

01:24.834 --> 01:28.291
<i>Amazingly bad.</i>

01:28.375 --> 01:30.625
- Morning.
- Morning.

01:32.083 --> 01:34.417
So last night...

01:34.500 --> 01:38.000
Yeah, I know. Wow.

01:39.166 --> 01:40.542
Super wow.

01:45.375 --> 01:47.250
Is that clock right?

01:47.333 --> 01:48.917
Oh, man, I gotta get to work.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.542
Yeah. I gotta get home.

01:52.834 --> 01:56.166
So... Well, we should do this again.

01:56.250 --> 02:00.792
Oh, definitely. This week
doesn't seem to be that great. Maybe...

02:00.875 --> 02:02.625
Next week, I'm swamped.

02:02.709 --> 02:06.291
Oh. Well, we'll figure something out.

02:06.375 --> 02:12.083
<i>It was at that moment Edie and Carlos</i>
<i>had the exact same thought.</i>

02:14.667 --> 02:15.792
Thank you.

02:15.875 --> 02:19.291
No. Thank you.

02:19.375 --> 02:23.125
<i>They would definitely</i>
<i>be having sex again.</i>

02:23.625 --> 02:27.041
<i>Just not with each other.</i>

03:10.625 --> 03:15.000
<i>It's so easy to spot the lonely ones.</i>

03:15.083 --> 03:16.667
It wasn't the first time...

03:16.750 --> 03:19.709
<i>They're the people</i>
<i>who tell stories to their plants...</i>

03:19.792 --> 03:21.208
I kind of like him.

03:21.291 --> 03:24.500
<i>...and whisper secrets to their pets...</i>

03:24.583 --> 03:26.083
Come on!
Luis ain't no basketball player!

03:26.166 --> 03:28.291
<i>...and have arguments with their TV.</i>

03:28.375 --> 03:31.250
He was running like his feet
are made out of lead!

03:31.333 --> 03:35.083
<i>And the loneliest of all</i>
<i>are the ones who talk to people.</i>

03:35.166 --> 03:36.542
You know what I think, Gilbert?

03:36.625 --> 03:39.333
<i>People who are no longer there.</i>

03:39.417 --> 03:40.959
Phone's gonna ring any second

03:41.041 --> 03:44.083
and it's gonna be Lynette begging me
to come over early.

03:45.375 --> 03:49.208
Did I tell you that Tom had surgery
on his back last week?

03:49.291 --> 03:53.667
Yep, that idiot's flat on his ass
while Lynette brings home the bacon

03:53.750 --> 03:55.375
again.

03:55.458 --> 03:57.083
I shouldn't judge.

03:57.166 --> 03:59.959
Plenty of people didn't get
what I saw in you.

04:00.041 --> 04:03.333
I won't name names. My sister Gayle.

04:04.667 --> 04:06.583
You know, I always told her

04:06.667 --> 04:10.500
that beneath all the name-calling
and the dish-throwing,

04:10.583 --> 04:12.291
we really loved each other.

04:14.041 --> 04:16.834
Bet you 50 bucks it's Lynette.

04:16.917 --> 04:18.750
Hello?

04:19.291 --> 04:21.417
You lose, Gilbert. What's up?

04:21.500 --> 04:23.000
I have to get to the restaurant early.

04:23.083 --> 04:26.125
Is there any way you could come over
and get the kids off to school?

04:26.208 --> 04:28.375
Hey, why am I seeing pyjamas?
Get dressed.

04:28.458 --> 04:31.709
Yeah, they are ready to go.
So what do you say?

04:31.834 --> 04:35.917
Oh, great. Thanks. I owe you big time.
Okay, bye.

04:36.000 --> 04:38.917
All right. I'm heading out of here.
Wish me luck.

04:39.000 --> 04:40.166
More interviews this morning?

04:40.250 --> 04:41.542
Yeah, but don't worry,

04:41.625 --> 04:44.375
I'm gonna find you
the assistant manager of your dreams.

04:44.458 --> 04:47.458
Are you sure? Because
the last 10 résumés you showed me...

04:47.542 --> 04:49.083
Yeah, I know, I know.

04:49.166 --> 04:51.000
Bottom of the barrel,
convicts and losers.

04:51.083 --> 04:52.333
You were clear about that last night.

04:52.417 --> 04:54.959
But make sure that they really know
how to wrangle the employees.

04:55.041 --> 04:57.375
Like Kim, she never buses her tables.

04:57.458 --> 05:00.291
- I'm the one that told you that.
- Oh, you're right.

05:00.375 --> 05:03.083
Hey, honey, I had an idea
about the specials for today.

05:03.166 --> 05:05.458
I was thinking
goat cheese and mushrooms.

05:05.542 --> 05:08.500
Oh, for God's sake, Tom!

05:11.792 --> 05:14.291
I'm gonna be late for the interviews.
I really should go.

05:14.375 --> 05:17.625
Honey, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
I know I am driving you crazy.

05:17.709 --> 05:21.250
It's just that I'm feeling so guilty
laying here, totally worthless,

05:21.333 --> 05:23.250
while you run the restaurant
and the house.

05:23.333 --> 05:26.875
It's okay. I am gonna find a way
to make this all work.

05:26.959 --> 05:28.667
And you just get better.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.667
Oh, Mrs McCluskey. Perfect timing.

05:31.750 --> 05:35.083
Hey, make sure you have
your cell phone with you.

05:35.166 --> 05:39.166
Then while you're interviewing,
I'll call, you can conference me in.

05:40.041 --> 05:42.417
That is a great idea.

05:44.583 --> 05:45.709
- Hi.
- Hi.

05:45.792 --> 05:47.667
At some point,
Tom's gonna ask you to look for this.

05:47.750 --> 05:49.625
You will not find it.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.458
Great. Love you.

05:56.542 --> 05:57.583
Here's your beer.

05:57.667 --> 06:01.375
Oh, good job, chipmunk.
No foam this time.

06:01.458 --> 06:04.208
I tipped the glass
just like you told me to.

06:04.291 --> 06:08.041
I think someone's ready
to salt his first margarita glass.

06:10.291 --> 06:13.208
Mommy, do you have trouble
going to sleep?

06:14.166 --> 06:15.542
No.

06:16.166 --> 06:17.333
Why do you ask?

06:17.417 --> 06:20.208
'Cause I heard Carlos say
you were bad in bed.

06:20.291 --> 06:21.750
What?

06:21.834 --> 06:24.667
Why'd he say that?
Do you have nightmares?

06:24.750 --> 06:27.750
Okay, sweetie, I need you to focus.

06:27.834 --> 06:31.625
What exactly did Carlos say,
and who did he say it to?

06:31.709 --> 06:33.750
I went to get my soccer ball
from his yard.

06:33.834 --> 06:36.291
He was on the phone
talking to someone.

06:36.375 --> 06:39.917
So what does "bad in bed" mean?

06:40.917 --> 06:45.000
Oh, it means
that you're not good at making

06:46.417 --> 06:48.375
your bed.

06:48.458 --> 06:50.875
And Mommy doesn't like people saying
she can't make a bed

06:50.959 --> 06:57.250
because, trust me, nobody makes
a bed as good as your mommy.

06:57.333 --> 07:00.667
If you want,
I can tell people you're good in bed.

07:01.333 --> 07:04.959
No, no, no. That's fine, sweetie.

07:05.041 --> 07:08.208
If you want to help Mommy,

07:08.959 --> 07:11.458
just top off her breakfast.

07:18.667 --> 07:22.792
Susan, I'm by the orange stand.
Where are you?

07:22.875 --> 07:24.375
The cheese stand.

07:24.458 --> 07:26.583
No, I don't mind you going back
for free samples,

07:26.667 --> 07:30.000
but if you like it so much,
why not just buy some?

07:30.333 --> 07:34.417
Yeah, of course, you're right.
It always tastes better when it's free.

07:34.500 --> 07:36.583
Okay, then, please hurry.

07:37.959 --> 07:39.875
Oh. Hello.

07:41.959 --> 07:43.083
Hey.

07:43.709 --> 07:46.250
Boy, you're everywhere these days.

07:46.709 --> 07:47.792
Excuse me?

07:47.875 --> 07:50.250
Yesterday Susan and I ran into you
at the post office.

07:50.333 --> 07:51.542
Last week, the movies.

07:51.625 --> 07:53.375
One might think you're following us.

07:53.458 --> 07:57.875
Trust me, one has better things to do
than follow you around.

07:59.125 --> 08:02.291
And yet here you are again.

08:03.959 --> 08:06.583
Ian, Fairview's a small town.

08:06.667 --> 08:09.333
You want distance? Move to the city.

08:18.000 --> 08:21.750
You've been awfully quiet since we left
the market. Is everything okay?

08:21.834 --> 08:26.667
Well, since you ask,
I'm having some problems at work.

08:26.750 --> 08:28.000
Really?

08:28.083 --> 08:32.250
Yes, we're in the midst
of some corporate restructuring.

08:32.333 --> 08:35.083
I'm gonna have to spend more time
in London.

08:35.583 --> 08:36.625
Oh.

08:38.291 --> 08:39.458
Okay.

08:40.333 --> 08:45.625
And I was thinking,
maybe you and I should just relocate.

08:46.750 --> 08:49.333
To London? Permanently?

08:49.417 --> 08:50.834
I know it's sudden, but...

08:50.917 --> 08:52.542
Yeah! It's sudden.

08:52.625 --> 08:54.667
My whole life is here. My friends...

08:54.750 --> 08:56.291
Julie is still in school.

08:56.375 --> 08:57.959
Susan!

09:16.000 --> 09:18.458
Oh, my God! Are you okay?

09:18.542 --> 09:20.542
I'm fine. I'm fine.

09:20.625 --> 09:26.375
Okay. I can feel the car sinking.
We're gonna have to get to shore.

09:29.208 --> 09:30.500
Ian?

09:30.583 --> 09:32.917
How deep do you think this water is?

09:34.709 --> 09:38.125
Deep enough. Come on, let's move!

09:38.959 --> 09:40.333
Susan,

09:41.625 --> 09:43.166
I can't swim.

09:43.542 --> 09:47.917
What? You...
You said you played water polo.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.125
I said polo! With horses!

09:50.208 --> 09:53.208
How can you not know how to swim?
Didn't you go to summer camp?

09:53.291 --> 09:55.375
I stayed in the canoe! Let it go!

09:55.458 --> 09:58.333
Okay, don't panic.

09:58.917 --> 10:02.208
Just grab onto my neck,
and I'll swim for the both of us.

10:02.291 --> 10:04.250
I'm twice your size. We might drown.

10:04.333 --> 10:07.500
Let's just stay here
and think of something else.

10:07.583 --> 10:09.667
If you stay here, you'll definitely drown.

10:09.750 --> 10:11.375
You see how my plan is better?

10:18.834 --> 10:21.625
Oh, look,
there's somebody on the shore!

10:23.250 --> 10:27.667
- It's Mike! He's here!
- Of course he is.

10:27.750 --> 10:29.375
Mike!

10:42.792 --> 10:45.417
Okay, okay, okay, I can walk from here!

10:45.500 --> 10:49.000
Sorry.
You were just gripping me so tight.

10:50.750 --> 10:54.583
Oh, my God. Mike, you saved our lives.

10:57.083 --> 10:58.625
And our cheese!

10:58.709 --> 11:04.375
Ian, can you believe it?
Mike saved our cheese.

11:04.458 --> 11:06.291
Yes. He's quite the hero.

11:06.375 --> 11:08.792
Yeah. Good thing I was following you.

11:14.667 --> 11:17.083
Arnie, thanks for coming in.

11:17.166 --> 11:19.792
We will definitely keep you in mind.

11:19.875 --> 11:24.166
Okay. Okay.

11:24.250 --> 11:26.959
Come on.
What was wrong with that guy?

11:27.583 --> 11:30.667
He kept asking what we do
with the food people don't eat.

11:30.750 --> 11:32.625
All right, so he's a fat loser.

11:32.709 --> 11:35.083
I mean, who'd you expect
to get for $8.50 an hour?

11:35.166 --> 11:37.208
Well, that's what we pay you,
and you seem happy enough.

11:37.291 --> 11:40.250
Well, that's because
I'm doing the beer delivery guy.

11:40.333 --> 11:44.125
Okay. My fault for asking.

11:47.250 --> 11:48.959
Rick Coletti?

11:49.041 --> 11:51.667
- That's me.
- Oh, great. Come on over.

11:53.375 --> 11:55.375
Your application?

11:55.583 --> 11:56.959
One second.

12:00.291 --> 12:02.750
That's been bothering me. Sorry.

12:02.834 --> 12:06.375
No, it's great. You can spell.
You are now officially the front-runner.

12:06.458 --> 12:08.875
Yeah, my grandma came over
from Naples.

12:08.959 --> 12:12.375
I've been making calzones
since before you were born.

12:12.458 --> 12:14.583
How old do you think I am?

12:15.291 --> 12:16.875
Thirty? Thirty-one?

12:17.542 --> 12:21.333
Not afraid to shamelessly ass-kiss.
You are doing very well.

12:21.417 --> 12:23.667
Great. You wanna skip ahead
to the part where you hire me?

12:23.750 --> 12:27.709
Well, I should probably take a look
at your application first.

12:28.500 --> 12:29.667
Okay.

12:30.667 --> 12:33.000
Okay, don't be afraid
if you don't have a tonne of experience.

12:33.083 --> 12:35.667
I realise for what we're paying,
we're not exactly gonna get a...

12:36.458 --> 12:37.500
Whoa!

12:38.166 --> 12:39.917
You were sous chef at Cucina?

12:40.000 --> 12:42.792
- Yeah.
- That's a five-star restaurant.

12:42.875 --> 12:45.959
- Actually, four.
- Which is four more than we have.

12:46.041 --> 12:51.208
Yeah, but this place has character
and charm, and a beautiful owner.

12:53.625 --> 12:55.583
Yeah, but seriously,

12:55.667 --> 12:58.542
why would a four-star chef wanna slum
at a pizza joint?

13:01.125 --> 13:04.917
Mrs McCluskey! Mrs McCluskey!

13:05.000 --> 13:07.458
I'm right here. Keep your shirt on.

13:07.542 --> 13:08.875
I need another pill.

13:08.959 --> 13:13.166
And please tell the kids
to turn down the TV.

13:13.250 --> 13:15.959
I yell, they turn it down.
I walk away, they turn it up.

13:16.041 --> 13:17.083
Vicious circle.

13:17.291 --> 13:20.291
Surely you can control five little kids.

13:20.375 --> 13:22.458
- Can I beat them?
- No.

13:22.542 --> 13:25.000
Then my hands are tied.

13:25.083 --> 13:29.959
Hi, I'm home! And I've got good news.
I found a new manager.

13:30.041 --> 13:31.458
- That's terrific.
- Yeah.

13:31.542 --> 13:35.834
His name is Rick Coletti
and he was a sous chef at Cucina.

13:35.917 --> 13:38.291
Cucina?
Why does he wanna work at our place?

13:38.375 --> 13:42.083
Yeah, I had that exact same thought.
And to be honest, he has a history.

13:42.166 --> 13:43.333
History?

13:43.417 --> 13:46.166
You know how stressful it is
working at a four-star restaurant.

13:46.250 --> 13:48.834
And he, like many chefs,
started using cocaine, just to...

13:48.917 --> 13:52.291
- Oh, no, no, no. No way.
- He's been clean for almost a year.

13:52.375 --> 13:54.041
We're not the Betty Ford clinic.

13:54.125 --> 13:56.375
No, I know, but I've got
a really good feeling about this guy.

13:56.458 --> 13:58.041
All he wants is a fresh start.

13:58.125 --> 14:00.750
I am not gonna hire a junkie
who's gonna turn around

14:00.834 --> 14:03.750
and then hock our jukebox
just to feed his habit.

14:03.834 --> 14:06.458
- Here. No, find somebody else.
- I can't find somebody else.

14:06.542 --> 14:07.959
I've interviewed 50 guys

14:08.041 --> 14:10.542
and this "junkie" happens
to be the best of the bunch.

14:10.625 --> 14:13.041
Seriously, Tom,
I don't know how much longer I can...

14:13.125 --> 14:14.834
Lynette, please,
can we just talk about this later?

14:14.917 --> 14:16.500
I'm in a lot of pain right now.

14:18.083 --> 14:20.083
I'm sorry.

14:20.166 --> 14:24.125
Please, just do what I am asking.

14:24.875 --> 14:29.125
Fine. I'll keep looking.

14:31.125 --> 14:32.333
Jerk.

14:34.750 --> 14:37.417
I had such a good time tonight.
Who knew you could dance?

14:37.500 --> 14:39.166
It's one of my many hidden talents.

14:39.250 --> 14:40.542
Tell you what.
You invite me in for a drink,

14:40.625 --> 14:43.333
- I'll show you another one.
- Not tonight, thanks.

14:43.417 --> 14:46.208
So you would tango with a man
and then not have sex with him?

14:46.291 --> 14:48.917
You know, that's actually
against the law in Argentina.

14:49.000 --> 14:51.333
Come on, we both know
it's gonna happen eventually.

14:51.417 --> 14:55.583
And every time you say that,
"eventually" gets a little further away.

14:55.667 --> 14:58.041
Stop begging, or I'm not going
to your rally tomorrow.

14:58.125 --> 14:59.875
Okay, fine. I can be patient.

14:59.959 --> 15:02.583
As far as I'm concerned,
the chase is half the fun.

15:02.667 --> 15:07.792
Half the fun?
Oh, honey, if I ever do say yes,

15:13.291 --> 15:17.458
you're gonna adjust
that percentage way down.

15:27.000 --> 15:30.125
You can't possibly be
eating more cheese.

15:30.208 --> 15:33.291
What? You've never heard
of a midnight snack?

15:33.917 --> 15:37.917
Unless you can think of something else
that I can nibble on.

15:39.625 --> 15:44.000
Slide over,
you cheddar-breathed tease.

15:50.875 --> 15:55.125
- Oh, what's that?
- Oh, it's a thank-you gift for Mike.

15:55.208 --> 15:56.250
Oh, okay.

15:57.208 --> 15:58.417
Correct me if I'm wrong,

15:58.500 --> 16:00.709
but didn't we already thank him
at the shore,

16:00.792 --> 16:02.458
and again when he dropped us off
at home?

16:02.542 --> 16:05.375
Well, I don't think
you can really thank somebody

16:05.458 --> 16:07.208
too many times for saving your life.

16:07.291 --> 16:08.834
Oh, I wish you'd stop saying that.

16:08.917 --> 16:11.000
- Saying what?
- That he saved my life.

16:11.083 --> 16:13.291
I'm fairly certain
I could've survived without his help.

16:13.375 --> 16:15.417
And if anyone did any life-saving,
it was me.

16:15.500 --> 16:17.083
- You?
- Yes.

16:17.166 --> 16:18.291
If I hadn't warned you about the deer,

16:18.375 --> 16:20.000
it would've gone straight
through the windshield,

16:20.083 --> 16:22.834
and you would've ended up
with an antler through your brain.

16:22.917 --> 16:24.000
Oh.

16:26.500 --> 16:27.792
Okay.

16:28.208 --> 16:30.542
- That's a good point.
- Thank you.

16:31.291 --> 16:33.959
But we were in a bit of a jam there,

16:34.875 --> 16:37.875
and I don't think you should be
embarrassed for needing a little help.

16:37.959 --> 16:41.166
I'm not embarrassed.
I don't feel emasculated either.

16:41.250 --> 16:47.083
Emasculated? Who said emasculated?
And why are you not kissing me now?

16:47.709 --> 16:49.667
I'm ready when you are.

16:58.125 --> 17:00.083
Oh, okay.

17:01.583 --> 17:06.583
I guess we're gonna cut right to the...
Whoa. Wow.

17:22.291 --> 17:25.000
Don't worry. It happens to everybody.

17:26.709 --> 17:31.417
- Maybe it would help to talk about it.
- No. I don't want to talk about it.

17:32.709 --> 17:36.458
All right. We won't talk about it.

17:42.291 --> 17:43.959
Want some cheese?

17:52.417 --> 17:53.500
Hey, how are you?

17:53.583 --> 17:59.083
I'm good.
You might not think so, but I am good.

17:59.458 --> 18:00.500
Huh?

18:01.500 --> 18:05.875
Where in the hell do you get off
telling people that I am bad in bed?

